---

Why AGPL-3.0 for the harness:

The protocol requires that the harness be open source (§4.7 of the SPEC).
AGPL-3.0 preserves this property downstream — anyone who modifies the
harness, including running a modified version over the network, must
publish their modifications under the same license. This is the structural
defense against the protocol invariants being silently broken by closed-
source forks operated as services.

A fork that needs a more permissive harness license for legitimate reasons
may negotiate with Harmonia for a dual-licensing arrangement. The
default is AGPL-3.0 and any departure from it is per-case.
